comments: Please note that due to a technical issue, this report was conducted with limited available video. Any subsequent changes will be noted in the comments.
James (LAL) avoids stepping out of bounds as he passes the ball along the baseline.
Sabonis (SAC) rolls towards the basket prior to marginal contact occurring with Schroder (LAL) after Schroder commits to going under the pick.
Schroder (LAL) brings his hands toward Fox's (SAC) path and marginal contact occurs with Fox's front as he drives inside the perimeter.
Fox (SAC) brings his off-arm outward slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with Schroder's (LAL) front as Fox spins away from the contact.

Sabonis (SAC) makes clean contact with the ball as simultaneous marginal contact occurs with Bryant (LAL) during the rebound, some of which occurs to Bryant's head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
James (LAL) pursues the rebound and incidental contact occurs with Barnes (SAC) during rebounding.

Bryant (LAL) brings his right arm forward as he continues to pursue the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Sabonis' (SAC) back and head when he gains control of it. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Bryant (LAL) turns into Sabonis' (SAC) body and initiates contact that affects his shot near the rim.
Barnes (SAC) brings his arm forward as he pursues the rebound and incidental arm contact occurs with Bryant (LAL) as Bryant gains control of the ball.
Murray (SAC) maintains a rested forearm on James' (LAL) front and marginal contact occurs as Murray fronts James in the post.
James (LAL) extends his forearm into Murray (SAC) and delivers contact to Murray's head that affects his ability to defend.
Fox (SAC) is bracing for the contact from Schroder (LAL) and marginal contact occurs as Fox (SAC) releases away from the contact.
Barnes (SAC) brings his hands toward James' (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs with James' front as he drives inside the perimeter.
Sabonis (SAC) moves forward into James' (LAL) body and initiates contact as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Lyles (SAC) establishes himself in Schroder's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Bryant (LAL) is moving alongside Fox's (SAC) path and marginal contact occurs with Fox's side as he dribbles inside the perimeter.
Schroder (LAL) is moving alongside Fox (SAC) when marginal contact occurs with Fox's side as he dribbles along the sideline.
Christie (LAL) legally contests Huerter's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAL) brings his arm backward and incidental arm contact occurs with Lyles (SAC) before Westbrook cleanly dislodges the ball away from him during rebounding.

Schroder (LAL) brings his left hand toward Fox's (SAC) right side and marginal contact occurs as the errant pass is thrown behind Fox. Schroder then makes clean contact with the ball after Fox deflects it and bats it toward mid-court as simultaneous incidental contact occurs.
Westbrook (LAL) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Schroder (LAL) and Fox (SAC) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Fox (SAC) touches the ball last before it goes out bounds.
Westbrook (LAL) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Murray (SAC) brushes Bryant's (LAL) arm and marginal contact occurs as Bryant is passing the ball.
Okpala (SAC) is moving forward slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Westbrook (LAL) as Westbrook splits the double team.
Mitchell (SAC) commits a take foul on Westbrook (LAL). The contact occurs prior to Westbrook's gather and continuation was correctly not awarded.
Schroder (LAL) moves somewhat laterally towards Fox (SAC) and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Schroder (LAL) legally contests Fox's (SAC) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Westbrook (LAL) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Westbrook (LAL) and Okpala (SAC) briefly engage and disengage off ball.  Any contact that occurs after the whistle is deemed immaterial.

Replay review of the foul called on Fox (SAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Fox turns and delivers body contact to Schroder's (LAL) side during the driving shot attempt, which is subsequently affected. The game clock was re-set to 0:03.6.
Westbrook (LAL) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Fox's (SAC) left arm after the release.
